{
  "texts": [
    "Graduate Management Admission Test (GMAT)The GMAT exam serves as a differentiating factor for more than 100,000 candidates every year during the business school admissions process, with a significant 90% of new MBA enrollments relying on a GMAT score [48].",
    "The GMAT exam is recognized as a reliable indicator of a student's potential for success.",
    "Each GMAT exam consists of 31 quantitative reasoning, 36 verbal reasoning, 12 integrated reasoning problems, and an analytical writing essay.",
    "The GMAT Total Score is derived from the Verbal and Quantitative sections of the exam.",
    "This Total Score is based on the test taker's calculated performance before the scores for the Quantitative Reasoning and Verbal Reasoning sections are assigned."
  ]
}